My Review: Very conflicted on my rating of this book. DNF'd at 80%. The author's writing style was incredibly captivating and really sucked you into the character's world. However, as many reviewers have already warned, this is a very heavy read! Although I found myself really wanting to continue on and know how the story ends, ultimately almost every time I read this book I came away feeling sad, anxious, triggered or all three. There were some really amazing comforting parts though.

Title: The Power of Habit: Why We Do What We Do in Life and Business
Author: Charles Duhigg
My Review:
4.5
Very interesting read! This book provided insightful and interesting anecdotes and studies related to the science of habits, how they are formed, how we can manipulate them and how much of it is really in our control. The author also included a practical guide at the end about how to implement the ideas presented.

Favourite Quote:
"For Aristole, habits reigned supreme. The behaviors that occur unthinkingly are the evidence of our truest selves, he said. So "just as a piece of land has to be prepared beforehand if it is to nourish the seed, so the mind of the pupil has to be prepared in its habits if it is to enjoy and dislike the right things"
